Here is a Cargo file for wtt.rs:

```
[package]
name = "wtt"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2021"

[dependencies]
chrono = "0.4"
serde = { version = "1", features = ["derive"] }
serde_json = "1"
structopt = "0.3"
```

This Cargo file specifies the name, version, and edition of the crate, as well as the dependencies it requires. The `chrono` dependency is used to work with dates and times, the `serde` and `serde_json` dependencies are used to serialize and deserialize data, and the `structopt` dependency is used to parse command-line arguments.
